Houses (or house-holds) are the original EVAs, because they need a living person inside to run them. Gene Wolfe was very interested in stories about ghost houses, appearing roadside as to lure someone inside. A fireplace is a house's engine organ. People also are sort of houses.

A house is a machine for immortality. Every sufficiently sophisticated machine hides a living being inside itself as a mechanical turk. A ghost house apparition is thus merely a living demonic entity taking the form of a house. LCL tastes like blood and EVAs hide living flesh.

Basically Gene Wolfe's "Many Mansions" story (which he literally intended to be read on Halloween) from "Gene Wolfe's Book of Days" was about Neon Genesis Evangelion, even though it wasn't even out yet. Both houses and EVAs are wombs, thus the Church is also a "she", like a ship.

In the past, there was almost a taboo against men who moved to their wife's household after marriage, instead of doing the opposite or building a house of their own. It operates under the same symbolism as Evola's "cursed cycle of procreation", or gynocracy. A return to the womb.

In a more deeply fallen world this translates to only entering a girl's room if it means her eventually entering your room. Every house has a gravity, like planest, and this is why saints levitate, as gravity is the physical law manifestation of Hell. There was no gravity in Eden
Basically keep in mind that deep underneath your city there are tunnels and cave systems and their structures and patterns actively affect your city's own arrangement and your day to day life
